{"tid":2423440,"cid":5,"subCid":10,"title":"眾議院通過全面的同性戀和跨性別平等立法","createTime":"2021-02-26T02:14:21.000Z","updateTime":"2021-02-26T12:29:01.000Z","uid":130626,"like":6,"dislike":4,"uniUserReply":15,"replies":[{"pid":"0f07293c47ef9a51f899719117599a32da698d14","tid":2423440,"uid":130626,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2021-02-26T02:14:21.000Z","msg":"WASHINGTON &mdash; A divided House on Thursday narrowly passed a bill that would extend civil rights protections to prohibit discrimination on the basis of sexual orientation or gender identity, but the measure faced an uphill battle to enactment, with Republicans almost uniformly opposed.<br />\n<br />\nThe legislation, passed 224 to 206 almost entirely along party lines, stands little chance of drawing enough Republican support in the Senate to advance, at least in its current form. It was the second time the Democratic-led House had passed the measure, known as the Equality Act, which seeks to amend the Civil Rights Act of 1964 to add explicit bans on discrimination against lesbian, gay, bisexual and transgender people in both public and private spaces.<br />\n<br />\n&ldquo;In most states, L.G.B.T.Q. people can be discriminated against because of who they are, or who they love,&rdquo; said Representative David Cicilline, an openly gay Democrat from Rhode Island and the lead sponsor. &ldquo;It is past time for that to change.&rdquo;<br />\n<a href=\"https://www.nytimes.com/2021/02/25/us/politics/house-equality-act-gay-rights.html\" data-sr-url=\"https://r.lihkg.com/link?u=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nytimes.com%2F2021%2F02%2F25%2Fus%2Fpolitics%2Fhouse-equality-act-gay-rights.html&d=6DLEtCU0DjtZYWozPjwd68dEKmWGZzYthIwftZf8Bt0%3D&h=b0fee9d7\" data-auto-link target=\"_blank\">https://www.nytimes.com/2021/02/25/us/politics/house-equality-act-gay-rights.html</a>"},{"pid":"e5a6a7c8397ffea1ce24cd07e6ef15a794ad177c","tid":2423440,"uid":25468,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":2,"replyTime":"2021-02-26T02:38: